<div id="review_1450559827" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1450559827" />
    <a title="Sookie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4136921-sookie"><img alt="Sookie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1599901105p2/4136921.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1450559827?book_show_action=true">Nov 23, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sookie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sookie" href="/user/show/4136921-sookie">Sookie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780141190280" href="/book/show/6632785-cat-on-a-hot-tin-roof">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4136921-sookie?shelf=plays">plays</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1450559827" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12275823687832783448">The play set in three acts is like a reality show focused on a family reunion. An ugly truth simmers silently, a continuous hum of &quot;mendacity&quot; that never increases or decreases in its pitch and the people living under the roof are all affected by it in one or the other way. Families can get messy, greedy, ugly and downright horrible. But they are family. <br/><br/>This is the story of one such family in cotton producing state. A rich family diseased with secrets and malcontent, happy children and connivin</span>
  <span id="freeText12275823687832783448" style="display:none">The play set in three acts is like a reality show focused on a family reunion. An ugly truth simmers silently, a continuous hum of "mendacity" that never increases or decreases in its pitch and the people living under the roof are all affected by it in one or the other way. Families can get messy, greedy, ugly and downright horrible. But they are family. <br /><br />This is the story of one such family in cotton producing state. A rich family diseased with secrets and malcontent, happy children and conniving daughter-in-laws, lovable big mama and sycophantic sons. There is greed, internalized homophobia, coming to terms with death of a great friend, seeking a lover, finding the perfect buzz - the moment when thinking shuts down; its of sons and fathers, of mother and son, of husbands and wives, jealousy and happiness.<br /><br />For what its worth, Maggie wants to stick with Brick knowing he isn't interested in her. Though she doesn't say, she understands the power Brick has over her in his absolute apathy towards her existence. She compares herself to a cat on hot tin roof: struggling to take a stand in a situation that is both dangerous and non-adaptable. She doesn't ask for permission. She just makes a decision and declares it. <br /><br />Maggie wants her husband Brick. Brink wants peace. Big Mama wants everyone in family to get along. Big Daddy wants Brick to stop drinking. Gooper, the other son, wants Big Daddy's estate. His wife Mae, wants what her husband wants. In this family everyone is after something and are sanctimonious about it when they express their desire. There are no heroes or villains here. There are no good or evil people in this story. They are ordinary people wanting something like every other human being. <br /><br />They are just as messy and as fucked up as the rest of us.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12275823687832783448" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

